Either that or Salazar is the pirate version of the Grim Reaper and the Devil's Triangle is just like his hideout.

I'm ok with both. Just give me a good tragic backstory!

I don't even think Captain Salazar is a pirate. 
As people have said before, Jack locked him inside devil's triangle, possibly because of trying to avoid Salazar capturing him.

And we can see that Salazar has a lot of medals on his robe, which could mean something as well. 
And his "mission" is to rid of every pirate in the world, which could be translated to - him hating pirates with a passion. 
People who think like that, are usually working for the "good" side. 
Maybe he was more of a pirate hunter or a navy commander/captain, before he was locked in devil's triangle by jack.

Just a thought.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment: I cannot believe it is here! I thought it was a fan-trailer at first. Glad to see its coming, though I have to say they are going darker - that I don't like about it - but a veteran movie go-er I know that things are not always as they seem. Sure hope its not in the theme of the fourth one. I didn't enjoy that one as I did the others. Then again going completely back to the fun loving elements of the first three would in itself be a mistake. I just hold great hopes that it ends the series on the great note it began on. So So many films series start out great but only get darker and darker and ultimately ruin - for me at least - what was once so great about them. I still hold out hope that Will and Elizabeth return one last time, too. Then again, my hopes for this film are no greater than those - and the fears that I hold - for the next HTTYD film. We can only go see and find out! True fans will go see it even if it turns out we don't like it. We love the old enough to give the new a try.

Comment:
Maybe this will suck, maybe it won't. But it will have great music. 

The problem is that they went from someone like Barbossa (charisma, likeable), Davy Jones (Tragic yet awesome) with cursed crew and his impressive kraken, to Blackbeard with a couple of Zombies and a regular crew. The fourth film was always going to feel like a big downgrade. 

Ghosts are somewhat generic but if they can capture the menace of Salazar like they did with Jones it will go a long way to being a decent movie. 

Pirates 1 = Fantastic
Pirates 2 = Great 
Pirates 3 = Average
Pirates 4 = Boring, uninspired, generic
Pirates 5 = ?

Comment: Okay I know it's crazy. But listen. Pause at 1:07. They all seem to be wearing a captain's hat, except the middle one who obviously can't wear a hat. Now, here comes my theory. The leader, Captain Salad (or whatever), picks up the souls of dead captains lost at sea, to join his crew. Now, look at the guy to the right at 1:07. Does that not look odly similliar to Lord Cutler Beckett? I mean, same hair, same hat, pretty much same suit, and he's bruised in such a way that he would probs look like, after his death at The Endeavour (his ship). Now, for Jack Sparrow. What if Captain Salad comes for him, thus the "Death comes straight for him", simply because Jack Sparrow have cheated death so many times? He escaped Davy Jones' locker once, and have cheated death several times. Captain Salad (or whatever he's named) is hunting down his long sought crew member! That's just my theory though :P

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
Hey Disney, here is a short list of things that I would like to see in a Pirates Of the Caribean movie.

1)A Sea Serpent. Retro scary cool monster.

2) Atlantis. Heck, you made up a whole language for the place in that animated movie. Might as well use it for atlantean characters. Adds world building atmosphere, internally advertises your properties, and the internet will eat up the "Oh, is Captain Jack in the same continuity as a Disney Cartoon?" stuff.

3) Tritons. No, not Ariel's dad. Look it up then make it up. You can make up a warrior race of fish people. Aqua Klingons. Have fun with that.

4)Grace O'mally references. When we historically have a Pirate Queen, it may be cool to have her in the film (she died in the 1600s, so add some magic to that), have a kickass grand daughter carrying on the family name, or have Jack hunt the treasure she left behind.

5) Search for the treasure of Sinbad. The movie writes itself. Get Deltoro to direct and he will stuff the film with Harrihousen monsters.

6)The likelihood of you going to japan is high for film novelty, so here are two things. A) Did you know off the northern coast of Japan there is a pyramid-like staircase leading deep underwater? Make up something with that. B) Did you know that eating Japanese mermaids can either turn you immortal or into a butt-ugly berserk monster? Story kinda writes itself. Free advertising if you have Jack Sparrow fighting a ninja.

7) Odyssey waters. You got Circi, Sirens, greek myth stuff all over the place, Add some Harpies that can fly and swarm a pirate ship and maybe have the treasure be the tomb of Poseidon or something else to make up. The last sword of Hephestus? Hm? Just remeber in the rich myth to have plenty of contemporary Mediterranean people and pirates.

((Jeeze, at this point just an animated series sounds better))

8) Baron Munchausen. Does not matter how he got there, but forcing Jack Sparrow to be someone else's straight man would be a great way to cap the series as he competes with the master of ridiculous legendary feats

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
Jesus. How many ghosts, demons, devils, demigods (whatever) has Jack faced, forgot and then conveniently come back into his life? "Hello Jack." -Captain Salazar "Jack... who's this!?" - Will Turner "(slurred speech) Oh him??? He was my old rum running partner that I left behind 20 years ago (and forgot to mention over the past decade) to be captured and tortured." Jack turns to Salazar, "sorry mate. No hard feelings, right!?!?" Dead silence in the theater except for one idiot who chuckles at the stale and recycled dialog. 
YAAAAAAWWWWNNN... Lemme guess, curses, double-crosses, "zany" dialog, noticeable CGI and the threat of no one actually dying. Man they're already pushing the use of 3D in the trailer. I'm a gonna guess.... 45% from critics.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment: This seems to promise a return to form. Bardem is a great actor. And the effects for him and his crew are really impressive and creepy. Tone also seems to be much darker, which is welcome (many forget the old movies had their share of horror moments, not just action/comedy). I like that it seems to be going back to the epic supernatural elements, like there were in the first three films. OST tried to backpedal on that, and it made it a visually uninteresting slog, after an entire trilogy of amazing sights and sounds. My fingers will be crossed for this one.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
There's a link to an old Easter Egg here, if you think about it.

DAVY: "Do you fear death?"
JACK: "You have no idea..."

Davy wasn't death; he simply transported the dead at sea to an eternal resting place (which later became more of a prison due to Davy's corruption and inability to keep doing his job). Davy bargained with men to delay their meeting with "Death".

Captain Salazar may, in fact, be Death (or his errand boy) coming for Jack. Given how many people have grudges with Sparrow, and how many stories surround him, it's quite possible he's been alive for several centuries eluding Death.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment: Ok so as I am watching this figure walk through the ship cutting down people, my immeadiate thought was that Will Turner had finally lost his mind and gone down the same road davey jones did, hunting down ships to add to his ranks. His face being hidden his long flowing hair always hiding him. leaving us to wonder. But then they show what must obviously be Will Turners son behind bars...on a british naval ship... And I then think, OH this isn't a monsterous attack, This is William coming to rescue his son. And as the music plays in a hauntingly similar fashion to davey jones theme, the figure walks down the steps and the look on that kids face, as though hes seeing someone he never expected to see.... and then bam the sword into the sparrow flyer... I was waiting for williams face to show behind it. But NO! For a split second we see what appears to be wills father bootstrape bill, and what looks like the sea life growth on his face returned. Its only when he steps into the light and says his name do we realize... this is someone new and this is a whole different game now. THATS how you do a mother f*cking trailer!

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
I'm so exited for Pirates Of The Caribbean 576. Seriously, just give up. Nobody likes this shitty series. The first film was loads of fun, the second and third made no goddamn sense and the fourth was just a shitty action movie. You're flogging a horse so dead its skeleton has decomposed. Realistically, many people will pay to see it, but that's just because they loved the first film and over-optimistically hope for a return to form, which will probably never happen. You'll get terrible reviews and you'll try again every five years, further embarrassing Disney and shitting all over the first film. It's seriously difficult to enjoy the first film knowing it's part of the same series as three (and probably now four) utter pieces of shit. Just use your budget to make a great original film. You'll probably get the same amount of money either way, but this way you'll have integrity. If you absolutely must 
turn this series into James Bond, just understand why everyone loves the first film. It's not because of its action, its fantasy, its deep and complex characters, or its many deep and complex subplots. It's simply because it's loads of fun. When you try to make a POTC film driven by those former elements, you epically fail. Please stop trying to be like Star Wars.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
Pros: Looks like it'll have a more focused narrative than the previous three had, the villains seem cool, and I especially love this kinda of "it's like they're constantly drowning" visual effect on them and I wonder how that plays into their story.

Cons: Looks like a retread of old narrative territory, undead/cursed pirates (Black Pearl) with a personal vendetta out looking for Jack (Dead Man's Chest) with the Navy caught in the crossfire (though that's just part for the course).

Whoa. This is darker than any of the last Pirates movies. Dark, creepy, and perhaps gritty. And I'm hyped up for it. :D

I also like how Captain Salazar seems like a Spanish pirate. When I started reading up on some history on piracy in the Caribbean, the initial victims were the Spanish merchants who were attacked by privateers from England which was a spillover from the conflict between England and Spain during Queen Elizabeth's time. Correct me if I'm wrong on that.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
My thoughts:
Javier Bardem is amazing actor, I am glad he was given a different look-he fits in with this franchise, but is not too similar to the skeletons, zombies, or Davey Jone's crew.
With the time taken into making this film, along with the return of characters and those related, it is clear this film will have a good amount going on. Not simply a race to a fountain with no real super-natural force beside one big scene (the mermaids) and a magic sword/ship. This is going to be "death in his wake" and battle time, for one reason or another. Stronger acting, not the very mellow, stand in blackbeard we got in 4. Ghosts, how do you stop them, hmmmm? The mood is also far more the tone of 1, 2, and 3.
In conclusion, from this, I believe this franchised has worked to learn, instead of simply hoping for another hit. I expect better 3D hopefully (don't be cheap disney) as well.

Title: Teaser Trailer: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Comment:
_Pirates of the Caribbean_ died with the second film.  They added too much supernatural crap and the threat/suspense of any character really dying.....well, died.
They tried to scale back a bit with the forth film and attempted to recreate a bit of the charm lost in _Curse of the Black Pearl_ (instead of the over-bloated complexity of 2 & 3).  It came out as "meh" and simply uninteresting.

Based on the teaser, this film looks no different.  Another supernatural underdead pirate guy with his "magic" crew is after Jack Sparrow and wants to kill him....supernaturally.  Wow, what a shock. -__-
(I was really really hoping that this teaser was Will Turner doing his work as Davy Jones but nope!)
